Element msdl:OrganizationDetailType / AggregateEchelon
Namespace No namespace
Annotations
 
Identifies the aggregate echelon level planned to in the scenario.
Diagram
Type msdl:enumEchelon
Properties
content simple
minOccurs 0
Facets
enumeration NONE 
No echelon indicated
enumeration TEAM 
Any unit smaller than a squad that will be denoted by a vehicle or weapon symbol in a graphical representation.
enumeration CREW 
Any unit smaller than a squad that will be denoted by a vehicle or weapon symbol in a graphical representation
enumeration SQUAD 
A small number of men, a subdivision or section of a company, formed for drill
enumeration SECTION 
A small tactical unit
enumeration PLATOON 
Basic administrative and tactical unit in most arms and services of the Army.
enumeration DETACHMENT 
Basic administrative and tactical unit in most arms and services of the Army.
enumeration COMPANY 
Basic administrative and tactical unit in most arms and services of the Army. A company is on a command level below a battalion and above a platoon.
enumeration BATTERY 
Basic administrative and tactical unit in fire support arms and services of the Army. A battery is on a command level below a battalion and above a platoon.
enumeration TROOP 
An aviation tactical organisation normally but not necessarily composed of aircraft of the same type.
enumeration BATTALION 
Unit composed of a headquarters and two or more companies or batteries. It may be part of a regiment and be charged with only tactical functions, or it may be a separate unit and be charged with both administrative and tactical functions.
enumeration SQUADRON 
Air: An administrative or tactical organisation normally but not necessarily composed of aircraft of the same type.  Maritime: An administrative or tactical organisation consisting of two or more divisions of ships, plus such additional ships as may be assigned as flagships or tenders.
enumeration REGIMENT 
Administrative and tactical unit, on a command level below a division or brigade and above a battalion, the entire organisation of which is prescribed by table of organisation.
enumeration GROUP 
An operational grouping which is based on either an infantry battalion or a tank regiment, each with at least a squadron or company of the other arm and with elements of other supporting arms and services allocated according to need..
enumeration BRIGADE 
Unit composed of a headquarters and two or more battalions. It may be part of an army and be charged with only tactical functions, or it may be a separate unit and be charged with both administrative and tactical functions.
enumeration DIVISION 
A tactical unit/formation that is a major administrative and tactical unit/formation that combines in itself the necessary arms and services required for sustained combat, larger than a regiment/brigade and smaller than a corps.
enumeration CORPS 
A formation larger than a division but smaller than an army or army group. It usually consists to two or more divisions together with supporting arms and services.
enumeration ARMY 
A formation larger than an army corps but smaller than an army group. It usually consists of two or more army corps.
enumeration ARMYGROUP 
The largest formation of land forces, normally comprising two or more armies or army corps under a designated commander.
enumeration FRONT 
The largest formation of land forces, normally comprising two or more armies or army corps under a designated commander.
enumeration REGION 
A grouping of two or more Army groups
Source
 
<xs:element name="AggregateEchelon" type="msdl:enumEchelon" minOccurs="0">
  <xs:annotation>
    <xs:documentation>Identifies the aggregate echelon level planned to in the scenario.</xs:documentation>
  </xs:annotation>
</xs:element>

Element msdl:MGRSType / MGRSPrecision
Namespace No namespace
Annotations
 
The precision used for each MGRS coordinate.  The precision is defined by assigning a value of 2 to define a number using kilometers as its units of measure; a value of 3 to define a number using 100 meters as its units of measure, a value of 4 to define a number using 10 meters as its units of measure, or a value of 5 to define a number using meters as its units of measure. The precision determines how the MGRS value is encoded (padded with leading zeros) in a fixed length string.
Diagram
Type msdl:integerMGRSPrecision1
Properties
content simple
Facets
maxInclusive 5
minInclusive 2
Source
 
<xs:element name="MGRSPrecision" type="msdl:integerMGRSPrecision1">
  <xs:annotation>
    <xs:documentation>The precision used for each MGRS coordinate. The precision is defined by assigning a value of 2 to define a number using kilometers as its units of measure; a value of 3 to define a number using 100 meters as its units of measure, a value of 4 to define a number using 10 meters as its units of measure, or a value of 5 to define a number using meters as its units of measure. The precision determines how the MGRS value is encoded (padded with leading zeros) in a fixed length string.</xs:documentation>
  </xs:annotation>
</xs:element>

Element msdl:METOCGraphicType / SymbolIdentifier
Namespace No namespace
Annotations
 
The 15 character Symbol identifier includes dashes for restricted fields that shall not be interpreted. These fields would be redundant to other explicit elements in the standard. Affiliation, Status, and Country Code are restricted in this manner. Affiliation and Country Code fields are provided in the ForceSide structure data. Status field value is 'Present' unless specified otherwise by the DateTimeGroup element.

Source

These fields would be redundant to other explicit elements in the standard. Affiliation, Status, and Country Code are restricted in this manner.   </xs:annotation>

Element msdl:UnitType / SymbolIdentifier
Namespace No namespace
Annotations
 
The 15 character Symbol identifier includes dashes for restricted fields that shall not be interpreted. These fields would be redundant to other explicit elements in the standard. Affiliation, Status, and Country Code are restricted in this manner. Affiliation and Country Code fields are provided in the ForceSide structure data. Status field value is 'Present' unless specified otherwise by the DateTimeGroup element.

Affiliation and Country Code fields are provided in the ForceSide structure data. Status field value is 'Present' unless specified otherwise by the DateTimeGroup element.</xs:documentation>
  </xs:annotation>

Graphic modifier that identifies Command level.
Diagram
Type msdl:enumEchelon
Properties
content simple
minOccurs 0
Facets
enumeration NONE 
No echelon indicated
enumeration TEAM 
Any unit smaller than a squad that will be denoted by a vehicle or weapon symbol in a graphical representation.
enumeration CREW 
Any unit smaller than a squad that will be denoted by a vehicle or weapon symbol in a graphical representation
enumeration SQUAD 
A small number of men, a subdivision or section of a company, formed for drill
enumeration SECTION 
A small tactical unit
enumeration PLATOON 
Basic administrative and tactical unit in most arms and services of the Army.
enumeration DETACHMENT 
Basic administrative and tactical unit in most arms and services of the Army.
enumeration COMPANY 
Basic administrative and tactical unit in most arms and services of the Army. A company is on a command level below a battalion and above a platoon.
enumeration BATTERY 
Basic administrative and tactical unit in fire support arms and services of the Army. A battery is on a command level below a battalion and above a platoon.
enumeration TROOP 
An aviation tactical organisation normally but not necessarily composed of aircraft of the same type.
enumeration BATTALION 
Unit composed of a headquarters and two or more companies or batteries. It may be part of a regiment and be charged with only tactical functions, or it may be a separate unit and be charged with both administrative and tactical functions.
enumeration SQUADRON 
Air: An administrative or tactical organisation normally but not necessarily composed of aircraft of the same type.  Maritime: An administrative or tactical organisation consisting of two or more divisions of ships, plus such additional ships as may be assigned as flagships or tenders.
enumeration REGIMENT 
Administrative and tactical unit, on a command level below a division or brigade and above a battalion, the entire organisation of which is prescribed by table of organisation.
enumeration GROUP 
An operational grouping which is based on either an infantry battalion or a tank regiment, each with at least a squadron or company of the other arm and with elements of other supporting arms and services allocated according to need..
enumeration BRIGADE 
Unit composed of a headquarters and two or more battalions. It may be part of an army and be charged with only tactical functions, or it may be a separate unit and be charged with both administrative and tactical functions.
enumeration DIVISION 
A tactical unit/formation that is a major administrative and tactical unit/formation that combines in itself the necessary arms and services required for sustained combat, larger than a regiment/brigade and smaller than a corps.
enumeration CORPS 
A formation larger than a division but smaller than an army or army group. It usually consists to two or more divisions together with supporting arms and services.
enumeration ARMY 
A formation larger than an army corps but smaller than an army group. It usually consists of two or more army corps.
enumeration ARMYGROUP 
The largest formation of land forces, normally comprising two or more armies or army corps under a designated commander.
enumeration FRONT 
The largest formation of land forces, normally comprising two or more armies or army corps under a designated commander.
enumeration REGION 
A grouping of two or more Army groups
Source
 
<xs:element name="Echelon" type="msdl:enumEchelon" minOccurs="0">
  <xs:annotation>
    <xs:documentation>Graphic modifier that identifies Command level.</xs:documentation>
  </xs:annotation>
</xs:element>

Element msdl:UnitModelType / Resolution
Namespace No namespace
Annotations
 
Enumeration indicating the level of fidelity appropriate for instancing the unit or equipment in the simulation.
Diagram
Type msdl:enumModelResolutionType
Properties
content simple
minOccurs 0
Facets
enumeration NONE 
No resolution/representation of the unit or equipment is neccesary to achieve scenario objectives.
enumeration MINIMAL 
Minimal resolution representation (graphical display only, no behaviors) of the unit or equipment is necessary to achieve scenario objectives.  This resolution typically applies to elements that are displayed as part of the common operating picture, but have no direct impact on scenario objectives.
enumeration STANDARD 
Standard (low) resolution representation of the unit or equipment necessary to achieve scenario objectives.  This resolution typically applies to elements that are two or more echelons above, below or adjacient to the principal planning unit.
enumeration ENHANCED 
Enhanced (medium) resolution representation of the unit or equipment necessary to achieve scenario objectives.  This resolution typically applies to elements that are within two echelons of the principal planning unit.
enumeration HIGH 
High resolution representation of the unit or equipment necessary to achieve scenario objectives.  This resolution typically applies to elements that are within one echelon of the principal planning unit.
enumeration NOT_SPECIFIED 
No resolution has been specified for the unit or equipment.
Source
 
<xs:element name="Resolution" type="msdl:enumModelResolutionType" minOccurs="0">
  <xs:annotation>
    <xs:documentation>Enumeration indicating the level of fidelity appropriate for instancing the unit or equipment in the simulation.</xs:documentation>
  </xs:annotation>
</xs:element>

Element msdl:EquipmentItemType / SymbolIdentifier
Namespace No namespace
Annotations
 
The 15 character Symbol identifier includes dashes for restricted fields that shall not be interpreted. These fields would be redundant to other explicit elements in the standard. Affiliation, Status, and Country Code are restricted in this manner. Affiliation and Country Code fields are provided in the ForceSide structure data. Status field value is 'Present' unless specified otherwise by the DateTimeGroup element.
Diagram
Type msdl:patternForceSymbolID15
Properties
content simple
Facets
length 15
pattern [S]{1}[\-]{1}[PAGMOSTUFVXLIZ\-]{1}[\-]{1}[A-Z\-]{6}[A-Z\-\*]{1}[A-Z\-\*]{1}[\-]{2}[AECGNSX\-\*]{1}
Source
 
<xs:element name="SymbolIdentifier" type="msdl:patternForceSymbolID15">
  <xs:annotation>
    <xs:documentation>The 15 character Symbol identifier includes dashes for restricted fields that shall not be interpreted. These fields would be redundant to other explicit elements in the standard. Affiliation, Status, and Country Code are restricted in this manner. Affiliation and Country Code fields are provided in the ForceSide structure data. Status field value is 'Present' unless specified otherwise by the DateTimeGroup element.</xs:documentation>
  </xs:annotation>
</xs:element>

Element msdl:EquipmentModelType / Resolution
Namespace No namespace
Annotations
 
Enumeration indicating the level of fidelity appropriate for instancing the unit or equipment in the simulation.
Diagram
Type msdl:enumModelResolutionType
Properties
content simple
Facets
enumeration NONE 
No resolution/representation of the unit or equipment is neccesary to achieve scenario objectives.
enumeration MINIMAL 
Minimal resolution representation (graphical display only, no behaviors) of the unit or equipment is necessary to achieve scenario objectives.  This resolution typically applies to elements that are displayed as part of the common operating picture, but have no direct impact on scenario objectives.
enumeration STANDARD 
Standard (low) resolution representation of the unit or equipment necessary to achieve scenario objectives.  This resolution typically applies to elements that are two or more echelons above, below or adjacient to the principal planning unit.
enumeration ENHANCED 
Enhanced (medium) resolution representation of the unit or equipment necessary to achieve scenario objectives.  This resolution typically applies to elements that are within two echelons of the principal planning unit.
enumeration HIGH 
High resolution representation of the unit or equipment necessary to achieve scenario objectives.  This resolution typically applies to elements that are within one echelon of the principal planning unit.
enumeration NOT_SPECIFIED 
No resolution has been specified for the unit or equipment.
Source
 
<xs:element name="Resolution" type="msdl:enumModelResolutionType">
  <xs:annotation>
    <xs:documentation>Enumeration indicating the level of fidelity appropriate for instancing the unit or equipment in the simulation.</xs:documentation>
  </xs:annotation>
</xs:element>

Element msdl:InstallationType / SymbolIdentifier
Namespace No namespace
Annotations
 
The 15 character Symbol identifier includes dashes for restricted fields that shall not be interpreted. These fields would be redundant to other explicit elements in the standard. Affiliation, Status, and Country Code are restricted in this manner. Affiliation and Country Code fields are provided in the ForceSide structure data. Status field value is 'Present' unless specified otherwise by the DateTimeGroup element.
Diagram
Type msdl:patternInstallationSymbolID15
Properties
content simple
Facets
length 15
pattern [S]{1}[\-]{1}[G]{1}[AP\-]{1}[I]{1}[A-Z\-]{5}[A-Z\-\*]{1}[A-Z\-\*]{1}[\-]{2}[AECGNSX\-\*]{1}
Source
 
<xs:element name="SymbolIdentifier" type="msdl:patternInstallationSymbolID15">
  <xs:annotation>
    <xs:documentation>The 15 character Symbol identifier includes dashes for restricted fields that shall not be interpreted. These fields would be redundant to other explicit elements in the standard. Affiliation, Status, and Country Code are restricted in this manner. Affiliation and Country Code fields are provided in the ForceSide structure data. Status field value is 'Present' unless specified otherwise by the DateTimeGroup element.</xs:documentation>
  </xs:annotation>
</xs:element>

Element msdl:TacticalGraphicType / SymbolIdentifier
Namespace No namespace
Annotations
 
The 15 character Symbol identifier includes dashes for restricted fields that shall not be interpreted. These fields would be redundant to other explicit elements in the standard. Affiliation, Status, and Country Code are restricted in this manner. Affiliation and Country Code fields are provided in the ForceStructure data. Status field value is 'Present' unless specified otherwise by the DateTimeGroup element.
Diagram
Type msdl:patternTacticalGraphicSymbolID15
Properties
content simple
Facets
length 15
pattern [G]{1}[\-]{1}[PAGMOSTUFVXLIZ\-]{1}[AP\-]{1}[A-Z\-]{6}[A-Z\-\*]{1}[A-Z\-\*]{1}[\-]{2}[AECGNSX\-\*]{1}
Source
 
<xs:element name="SymbolIdentifier" type="msdl:patternTacticalGraphicSymbolID15">
  <xs:annotation>
    <xs:documentation>The 15 character Symbol identifier includes dashes for restricted fields that shall not be interpreted. These fields would be redundant to other explicit elements in the standard. Affiliation, Status, and Country Code are restricted in this manner. Affiliation and Country Code fields are provided in the ForceStructure data. Status field value is 'Present' unless specified otherwise by the DateTimeGroup element.</xs:documentation>
  </xs:annotation>
</xs:element>

Element msdl:AreaSymbolModifiersType / Echelon
Namespace No namespace
Annotations
 
Graphic modifier that identifies Command level.
Diagram
Type msdl:enumEchelon
Properties
content simple
minOccurs 0
Facets
enumeration NONE 
No echelon indicated
enumeration TEAM 
Any unit smaller than a squad that will be denoted by a vehicle or weapon symbol in a graphical representation.
enumeration CREW 
Any unit smaller than a squad that will be denoted by a vehicle or weapon symbol in a graphical representation
enumeration SQUAD 
A small number of men, a subdivision or section of a company, formed for drill
enumeration SECTION 
A small tactical unit
enumeration PLATOON 
Basic administrative and tactical unit in most arms and services of the Army.
enumeration DETACHMENT 
Basic administrative and tactical unit in most arms and services of the Army.
enumeration COMPANY 
Basic administrative and tactical unit in most arms and services of the Army. A company is on a command level below a battalion and above a platoon.
enumeration BATTERY 
Basic administrative and tactical unit in fire support arms and services of the Army. A battery is on a command level below a battalion and above a platoon.
enumeration TROOP 
An aviation tactical organisation normally but not necessarily composed of aircraft of the same type.
enumeration BATTALION 
Unit composed of a headquarters and two or more companies or batteries. It may be part of a regiment and be charged with only tactical functions, or it may be a separate unit and be charged with both administrative and tactical functions.
enumeration SQUADRON 
Air: An administrative or tactical organisation normally but not necessarily composed of aircraft of the same type.  Maritime: An administrative or tactical organisation consisting of two or more divisions of ships, plus such additional ships as may be assigned as flagships or tenders.
enumeration REGIMENT 
Administrative and tactical unit, on a command level below a division or brigade and above a battalion, the entire organisation of which is prescribed by table of organisation.
enumeration GROUP 
An operational grouping which is based on either an infantry battalion or a tank regiment, each with at least a squadron or company of the other arm and with elements of other supporting arms and services allocated according to need..
enumeration BRIGADE 
Unit composed of a headquarters and two or more battalions. It may be part of an army and be charged with only tactical functions, or it may be a separate unit and be charged with both administrative and tactical functions.
enumeration DIVISION 
A tactical unit/formation that is a major administrative and tactical unit/formation that combines in itself the necessary arms and services required for sustained combat, larger than a regiment/brigade and smaller than a corps.
enumeration CORPS 
A formation larger than a division but smaller than an army or army group. It usually consists to two or more divisions together with supporting arms and services.
enumeration ARMY 
A formation larger than an army corps but smaller than an army group. It usually consists of two or more army corps.
enumeration ARMYGROUP 
The largest formation of land forces, normally comprising two or more armies or army corps under a designated commander.
enumeration FRONT 
The largest formation of land forces, normally comprising two or more armies or army corps under a designated commander.
enumeration REGION 
A grouping of two or more Army groups
Source
 
<xs:element name="Echelon" type="msdl:enumEchelon" minOccurs="0">
  <xs:annotation>
    <xs:documentation>Graphic modifier that identifies Command level.</xs:documentation>
  </xs:annotation>
</xs:element>

enumeration SQUADRON 
Air: An administrative or tactical organisation normally but not necessarily composed of aircraft of the same type.  Maritime: An administrative or tactical organisation consisting of two or more divisions of ships, plus such additional ships as may be assigned as flagships or tenders.
enumeration REGIMENT 
Administrative and tactical unit, on a command level below a division or brigade and above a battalion, the entire organisation of which is prescribed by table of organisation.
enumeration GROUP 
An operational grouping which is based on either an infantry battalion or a tank regiment, each with at least a squadron or company of the other arm and with elements of other supporting arms and services allocated according to need..
enumeration BRIGADE 
Unit composed of a headquarters and two or more battalions. It may be part of an army and be charged with only tactical functions, or it may be a separate unit and be charged with both administrative and tactical functions.
enumeration DIVISION 
A tactical unit/formation that is a major administrative and tactical unit/formation that combines in itself the necessary arms and services required for sustained combat, larger than a regiment/brigade and smaller than a corps.
enumeration CORPS 
A formation larger than a division but smaller than an army or army group. It usually consists to two or more divisions together with supporting arms and services.
enumeration ARMY 
A formation larger than an army corps but smaller than an army group. It usually consists of two or more army corps.
enumeration ARMYGROUP 
The largest formation of land forces, normally comprising two or more armies or army corps under a designated commander.
enumeration FRONT 
The largest formation of land forces, normally comprising two or more armies or army corps under a designated commander.
enumeration REGION 
A grouping of two or more Army groups
Source
 
<xs:element name="Echelon" type="msdl:enumEchelon" minOccurs="0">
  <xs:annotation>
    <xs:documentation>Graphic modifier that identifies Command level.</xs:documentation>
  </xs:annotation>
</xs:element>

Element msdl:MOOTWGraphicType / SymbolIdentifier
Namespace No namespace
Annotations
 
The 15 character Symbol identifier includes dashes for restricted fields that shall not be interpreted. These fields would be redundant to other explicit elements in the standard. Affiliation, Status, and Country Code are restricted in this manner. Affiliation and Country Code fields are provided in the ForceSide structure data. Status field value is 'Present' unless specified otherwise by the DateTimeGroup element.

These fields would be redundant to other explicit elements in the standard. Affiliation, Status, and Country Code are restricted in this manner. Affiliation and Country Code fields are provided in the ForceSide structure data. Status field value is 'Present' unless specified otherwise by the DateTimeGroup element.</xs:documentation>
  </xs:annotation>

  </xs:annotation>
  <xs:all>

      </xs:annotation>
    </xs:element>

      <xs:annotation>
        <xs:documentation>The MGRS one hundred thousand meter grid square designator, as defined by NIMA TM 8358.1.</xs:documentation>
      </xs:annotation>
    </xs:element>
    <xs:element name="MGRSPrecision" type="msdl:integerMGRSPrecision1">
      <xs:annotation>
        <xs:documentation>The precision used for each MGRS coordinate. The precision is defined by assigning a value of 2 to define a number using kilometers as its units of measure; a value of 3 to define a number using 100 meters as its units of measure, a value of 4 to define a number using 10 meters as its units of measure, or a value of 5 to define a number using meters as its units of measure. The precision determines how the MGRS value is encoded (padded with leading zeros) in a fixed length string.</xs:documentation>
      </xs:annotation>
    </xs:element>
    <xs:element name="MGRSEasting" type="msdl:integerMGRSEasting5">
      <xs:annotation>
        <xs:documentation>The easting component of the MGRS coordinate to the precision value of the MGRS precision element.</xs:documentation>

    </xs:element>
    <xs:element name="MGRSNorthing" type="msdl:integerMGRSNorthing5">
      <xs:annotation>
        <xs:documentation>The northing component of the MGRS coordinate to the precision value of the MGRS precision element.</xs:documentation>
      </xs:annotation>
    </xs:element>
    <xs:element name="ElevationAGL" type="msdl:floatElevationAGL6_2" minOccurs="0">
      <xs:annotation>
        <xs:documentation>The text modifier for units, equipment, and installations that displays the altitude portion of GPS; flight level for aircraft; depth for submerged objects; height for equipment or structures on the ground.</xs:documentation>
      </xs:annotation>
    </xs:element>
  </xs:all>
